OL,3,CChildren's books pulled from schools
OL,4,Cover pornographic weblink
OL,6,FA series of children's books has been
OL,7,Fpulled from school libraries after a
OL,8,Fweb address printed in the back was
OL,9,Ffound to link to pornographic content.
OL,11,FThe Spy Dog, Spy Pups and Spy Cat
OL,12,Fbooks by author Andrew Cope, from
OL,13,FDerby, are aimed at children of
OL,14,Fprimary school age.
OL,16,FA URL inside the books was meant to
OL,17,Fdirect readers to a website featuring
OL,18,Fbonus content, but the address now
OL,19,Ftakes children to a site with
OL,20,Finappropriate material.
